VFW Food Drive Event Plan

Event Date:
October 10, 2026

Expected Attendees:
Volunteers: 30
Community Members Receiving Assistance: 150
Total Expected Attendance: 180

Food Requirements:

Canned Vegetables – 250 cans
Canned Soup – 200 cans
Rice – 150 kg
Pasta – 100 kg
Peanut Butter – 120 jars
Cereal – 180 boxes
Bottled Water – 500 bottles
Fresh Produce Assortment – 300 kg

Supply Budget:
Item	Estimated Cost
Food Purchases	$2,500
Packaging Materials	$400
Transportation	$350
Volunteer Supplies	$200
Advertising and Outreach	$150
Miscellaneous expenses	$300

Total Budget: $3,900

Event Objectives:
Provide food assistance to local families.
Collect donations from community partners.
Increase awareness of food insecurity issues.
Encourage volunteer participation.

Event Coordinator:
John Smith
Location:
VFW Community Hall

Notes:
Donations accepted from 8:00 AM to 12:00 PM. Food distribution begins at 1:00 PM and ends at 4:00 PM. Volunteers should arrive by 7:30 AM for setup.